==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[aero-]]'', combining form for '''air''' + Latin ''[[planum]]'', '''flat'''

===Noun===
'''aeroplane''' (''British'') (''plural'' '''aeroplanes''')

====Variants====
*[[airplane]] (''US'')

# A powered [[aircraft]] with fixed [[wing]]s used for [[transportation]] of humans and goods; for [[amusement]] or [[entertainment]]; and in [[warfare]].

